{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"saucepan, aluminium foil, baking dish, colander, oven","id":"r247600","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-kVDEGEvf8fU\/XZMyjEqhJ2I\/AAAAAAAAamY\/5IJJBIG6mc0gNGG8-YCff2197VTxY2negCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_GzbnwegRj7try0rv.png","title":"Three Cheese Conchiglioni with Tomato Sauce - Conchiglioni ai tre formaggi e salsa al pomodoro","publishedAt":"2018-05-28T00:00:00Z","ingredients2":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pasta"},{"content":"100 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"content":"20 fresh basil leaves, plus extra for serving"},{"content":"250 g ricotta cheese"},{"content":"1 medium egg"},{"content":"1 pinch ground black pepper"},{"content":"100 g onions, quartered"},{"content":"2 garlic cloves"},{"content":"30 g olive oil"},{"content":"600 g tinned chopped tomatoes"},{"content":"1 tsp sugar"},{"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"content":"2 tsp fine sea salt, plus 1 pinch"},{"content":"water, for cooking pasta"},{"content":"16 conchiglioni rigati (large pasta shells)"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"125 g mozzarella, sliced (1 cm)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"44 g","fat":"39.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"31.5 g","calories":"2813 kJ \/ 674 kcal"},"preparations2":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Pasta and Filling"},{"content":"Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place 10 basil leaves in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add ricotta, egg, 1 pinch salt, pepper and 50 g reserved grated Parmesan then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place onions, garlic and oil in mixing bowl, chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b> then sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, remaining 10 basil leaves, sugar, pepper and 1 tsp salt then cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 200°C and bring a large saucepan of water with remaining 1 tsp salt added to the boil. Cook conchiglioni according to packet instructions, or until al dente. Drain pasta well using a colander and set aside to cool."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Assembly"},{"content":"Pour half the tomato sauce over the bottom of a baking dish. Spoon approx. 1 Tbsp ricotta mixture into cooled pasta shells, then arrange shells in baking dish, open side up."},{"content":"Pour over remaining tomato sauce, sprinkle with remaining 50 g grated Parmesan and top with sliced mozzarella. Cover with foil and bake for 35 minutes (200°C) then remove foil and bake uncovered for a further 5 minutes (200°C)."},{"content":"Scatter with fresh basil leaves before serving immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan cheese for a vegetarian hard cheese.","Often called ‘shells’ because of their shape, conchiglie are a type of pasta named after the Italian word for seashell – <i>‘conchiglia’<\/i>. There are three different sizes of shell and each is associated with specific dishes. This recipe features conchiglioni, the biggest, and because of their jumbo size, they are perfect for stuffing and serving <i>‘al forno’<\/i>. Filled with a delicious mix of ricotta and Parmesan, the conchiglioni are nestled in a vibrant tomato sauce and then baked, resulting in a cheesy dish that brings new meaning to ‘cheese and tomato pasta’."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 30m","4 portions"]}